The same strategy may be followed at any order of the 1=N expansion provided that the \Lambda dependence of the bare couplings are known to the same order in the covariant treatment. This is an enormous technical simplification over standard adiabatic expansion methods for removing the cut-off dependence explicitly.

In *\Phi 4 theory the general renormalization algorithm beyond lowest order requires knowledge of the OE2O/ vertex and OE-wavefunction renormalization constants Z1 and Z2 respectively, as well as the coupling renormalization Z*. The first two of these are defined in terms of the effective action by the conditions,

