If there is no mean value of the Dirac field, the Ward Identity guarantees that wavefunction and vertex renormalization drops out of the Maxwell equations for the mean field and that the charge renormalization Ze(\Lambda ; m) alone is sufficient to arrive at cut-off independent time evolution for the potential. To prove this we make use of several facts from the standard covariant analysis. First, we recall that the inverse propagator and vertex functions satisfy the Schwinger-Dyson equations,

